children.subject: I'm in the same boat more or less.  There aren't many seats assigned for declared; a lot more for undeclared, so chances are we'll be waitlisted for Phase 2.  However, it doesn't really matter that much because I think the class will expand eventually to bring everyone in, and there will be enough time to pick and choose the discussion/lab times.  At least that's the hope.

history.content:
EDIT: For fall 2019 classes 

Considering the class is broadcasted and there's no priority in initial registration for selecting discussion times just like 61a, is it fine to phase 2 CS61b while phase 1ing my other classes? Or would this be catastrophic if I end up not being able to enroll in 61b? I don't want to be waitlisted either obviously and I'm an EECS major if that matters.
